verbose_text: These mutations result in increased levels of Ras bound to guanosine triphosphate (GTP), promoting a hyper-proliferative state by the activation of, among others, Mek / Erk and Akt / mTOR (mammalian target of rapamycin) signaling pathways via the effector protein Raf and phosphatidylinositol 3-kinase (PI3K).
